        div(class="container")
            h1(class="text-center") Timestamp Microservice!
            
            div(class="row")
                div(class="col-xs-8 col-xs-offset-2")
                    h3 This is a timestamp microservice build as part of the backend development certification of FreeCodeCamp.
                div(class="col-xs-6 col-xs-offset-3")
                    h4 Here are the specific user stories you should implement for this project:
                    
                    p User Story: I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016).
                    
                    p User Story: If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
                    
                    p User Story: If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
                    
                    p Once you've finished implementing these user stories, click the "I've completed this challenge" button and enter the URLs for both your GitHub repository and your live app running on Heroku.
                    
                    p You can get feedback on your project by sharing it with your friends on Facebook.
                    
                    h4 Example usage:
                    p https://timestamp-microservice-burfield.c9users.io/December%2015,%202015
                    p https://timestamp-microservice-burfield.c9users.io/1450137600
                    h4 Example output:
                    code { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
        
